# Frontend standards

## Documentation first

When adding a new feature or choosing an implementation approach, read the **official documentation** for the relevant technology (Svelte, SvelteKit, MDN for HTML/CSS/JS) and follow current best practices.

## Design constraints

- **No third-party CSS frameworks** (no Tailwind, Bootstrap, etc.).
- **No third-party component libraries** (no shadcn, MUI, etc.).
- Keep the design **simple and custom** — plain CSS, minimal layout, clear typography.

## API contract

Backend API is documented at `/home/devl0pr/entertainment/onepoint/docs` (`openapi.yaml`).

- Match request/response shapes to the OpenAPI spec.
- Default API base URL: `http://localhost:8088`.
- Auth: Bearer token from login; see OpenAPI `securitySchemes.bearerAuth`.

## Code style

- **JavaScript only** — no TypeScript.
- Svelte 5 runes in new components.
- API calls through `src/lib/api/client.js`.
- Accessible forms: `<label>`, semantic HTML, visible error messages.
